Deploying a Node.js Website Using Docker on AWS EC2


Step -1:-

Setting up the AWS instance:-

Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) provides scalable compute capacity in the cloud, allowing users to run virtual servers. For this project, we assume:

-Instance Type: t2.micro (Free Tier eligible)
-OS: Amazon Linux 2 or Ubuntu 20.04
-Security Group: Open port 80 and port 3000 (for Node.js)
-IAM Role: Ensure EC2 has permissions to pull Docker images if needed

